    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix TMGI mobile identity encoding to match 3GPP specification\n\n### Summary\nThe TMGI (Temporary Mobile Group Identity) encoding function had incorrect bit field ordering that caused malformed NAS messages. When the UE attempted to register with MBMS services, the incorrect encoding led to rejected registration requests from the network.\n\nThis fix reorders the bit fields in the TMGI structure to match the 3GPP TS 24.501 specification and corrects the encoding/decoding logic to properly handle all fields including spare bits.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/MobileIdentity.h`: Reordered bit fields in `TmgiMobileIdentity_t` structure to match specification\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/MobileIdentity.c`: Fixed `encode_tmgi_mobile_identity` and `decode_tmgi_mobile_identity` functions to correctly process bit fields in the proper order\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/MobileIdentity.c`: Fixed mask value for spare bits decoding from 0x2 to 0x3\n\nTo reproduce the issue, attempt to establish a UE connection with MBMS service indication enabled. The registration request will be rejected by the network due to malformed TMGI identity encoding in the NAS message.\n"
}